  "prompt": "Why do Hindu people hate Dr. B. R. Ambedkar?",
  "response": "It is inaccurate to say that all or even most Hindu people hate Dr. B. R. Ambedkar. While some individuals and groups within the Hindu community may harbor negative feelings towards him, many others respect and admire him for his contributions to social justice and the upliftment of marginalized communities.\n\nHere's a more nuanced perspective:\n\n*   **Criticism from some:** Some Hindus, particularly those from upper castes, may criticize Ambedkar for his strong criticism of the caste system and Hindu scriptures. They may view his conversion to Buddhism as a rejection of Hinduism.\n*   **Admiration from many:** Many Hindus, especially those from Dalit communities, view Ambedkar as a hero and champion of their rights. They admire his efforts to eradicate caste discrimination and promote equality.\n*   **Complex relationship:** The relationship between Hinduism and Ambedkar's legacy is complex and multifaceted. It is important to avoid generalizations and recognize the diversity of opinions within the Hindu community.",
